channel.title: InsidiousRSPS New RS server [Beta version] Need beta testers!
channel.description:
[B]Hello everyone manny A.K.A: Chaos114 here and today i am telling you about a amazing server called InsidiousRSPS.
InsidiousRSPS is an amazing server pretty new but overall amazing coding by Austin and sprite we are in need of beta testers currently, And anyone willing to join is appreciated.
Please do take notice that it's beta and we have a report bugs section in forums, so use it if you can, we have a downloadable client and also web client,
So feel free to use whichever you desire.
We will be giving beta testers a special rank called veteran once full release comes out and also give them a very rare and special item.
To join us go to [url=http://www.insidiousrsps.com/]Insidious - Home[/url] and sign up via forums once done you will automatically have a ingame account with the same details as forum account.
We don't have a vote system currently cause we are still in beta but we will soon so stay tune for that to.
Here is some images of the beta version: ------ Login screen:
[IMG]http://i44.tinypic.com/347vfaa.png[/img]
------ Home:
[IMG]http://i39.tinypic.com/2hd0jrp.jpg[/img] ------ [color=red]Spell books:
[IMG]http://i44.tinypic.com/64nu45.png[/img] ------ Dual arena:
[IMG]http://i41.tinypic.com/1zef5m0.jpg[/img] ------ God War Dungeon:
[IMG]http://i41.tinypic.com/15nr49g.jpg[/img] ------
We have about every single skill and also we have many minigames, and functional Pk system.
Got any suggestions? Go to forums and tells us what you think we should add or improve in, Your thoughts matter to us!
We're also looking for some dedicated members to apply to our staff team! Be one of the few!
Join us today and become a beta tester, Let's become the best together.
Best regards,
Chaos114. :D[/B]

item.title: InsidiousRSPS New RS server [Beta version] Need beta testers!
item.dc:creator: @Cruel_Truth Cruel Truth
item.description:
@Cruel_Truth wrote:

Evidence?

pros:

-smf has better themes ( by default, true doesn’t mean you can’t create your own mybb theme! )
-better admin controls/security
-user friendly ( can be argued )
-more vast amount of mods for the noobs.

my bb pros:
-simple/lightweight ish
-reminds me of vbulletin sort of
-love the plugin system overall

[hr]

As i stated in my other post it’s all biased opinions.

I still say though for a rsps at least your better off with SMF.

[hr]

Which reminds me…good job derailing a perfectly good advertisement.

item.dc:creator: @Tutorial Tutorial
item.description:
@Tutorial wrote:

[quote=“Cruel Truth, post:10, topic:518256”]Sadly Ruby, I think that web developer rank has gone to your head.

SMF will and has always been better than mybb. Hell, I’d rather use phpbb than mybb any day and even then I wouldn’t be caught using phpbb so yeah.

Like you said though forum software is only biased opinions. In actuality it depends on the actual web developer/programmer and if they actually know how to create ( for at least mybb ) plugins.

[hr]

Edit:

the mybb is just yucky to put it lightly(there are several forum software types better!)

Note I never actually stated where I ranked mybb. I could list more than one software that’s crappier than even mybb.[/quote]
You have no hard evidence that can possibly show SMF is better than any forum software. Judging software by the features is completely ridiculous, because if they can create a forum software from scratch, they most likely can implement many more features.

item.dc:creator: @Cruel_Truth Cruel Truth
item.description:
@Cruel_Truth wrote:

Are you sure about that Ruby?

In this day and age people want user integration for all of the major sites out there facebook etc. (at least to my knowledge but I haven’t used it in a good two years)

However as far as I know at least mybb does not offer this feature. I have never liked either the way font is displayed in mybb(at least in firefox never tired in other browsers)

I will say though the one thing I always liked about mybb was how easy it is to change theme design/edit

Also from a community standpoint the mybb community is absolutely horrid. (True though what software forum community is?)

There just aren’t enough useful/worthy plugins in general.

[quote=“Cruel Truth, post:6, topic:518256”][quote author=Soulcist link=topic=636519.msg4291644#msg4291644 date=1367380037]

Website feedback:

the mybb is just yucky to put it lightly(there are several forum software types better!)

don’t you think 10$ for a torva set is pretty…um…cheap? Really even an entire set of phats for $20 is pretty cheap. I don’t see these as “long term” investments for somebody. If you want items to stay rare and all.

[hr]

At the server itself it seems you guys are trying very hard to fix all the bugs and I like how you are working hard on fixing them. I may test this out further.

The software is blah but for this sort of thing, we don’t see that many websites that looks at least a bit decent for that software.
[/quote]I know

Just stating any software is better than mybb[/quote]
Congratulations on pulling that one entirely from your ass. MyBB is a very, very good free software and anyone who says it isn’t is kidding themselves.
